			"content": {
				"id": "ALAS2022-2022-174",
				"title": "Amazon Linux 2022 - ALAS2022-2022-174: Medium priority package update for cryptsetup",
				"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2022 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2021-4122:\n\tIt was found that a specially crafted LUKS header could trick cryptsetup into disabling encryption during the recovery of the device. An attacker with physical access to the medium, such as a flash disk, could use this flaw to force a user into permanently disabling the encryption layer of that medium.\n",
